data.enText: to tend to think or behave in a particular way; to make sb do this

data.chText: 我倾向于认为我们在这个阶段不应采取行动。
data.enText: I incline to the view that we should take no action at this stage.

data.chText: 政府的效率比我们所惯常以为的要高。
data.enText: The government is more effective than we incline to think.

data.chText: 缺钱使很多年轻人产生了犯罪倾向。
data.enText: Lack of money inclines many young people towards crime.

data.chText: 他满脸的真诚，让我愿意相信他。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: His obvious sincerity inclined me to trust him.

data.chText: 点头（尤指以示同意、欢迎等）
data.enText: to bend your head forward, especially as a sign of agreement, welcome, etc.
to lean or slope in a particular direction; to make sth lean or slope
The land inclined gently towards the shore.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 使… + clin 倾斜 + e → 倾斜；倾向

means: 点头(尤指以示同意、欢迎等)

ex.chText: 只有当这架望远镜以30度角倾斜时，你才能看到那颗星星。
ex.enText: Only when the telescope is inclined at an angle of thirty degrees can you see that star.

ex.chText: 墙好像倾斜了将近15度角。
ex.enText: The wall seems to incline almost fifteen degrees.

synonyms.bx: 指（使）某物以某种角度或向某一方向倾斜。

ex.chText: 他身体前倾，想听他们在谈论什么。
ex.enText: He leaned forward and tried to catch what they were talking about.

ex.chText: 她正倚着一棵树等她男朋友。
ex.enText: She was leaning against a tree, waiting for her boyfriend.

ex.chText: 别把自行车斜靠在门上。
ex.enText: Don't lean your bicycle against the door.

synonyms.bx: 指某人身体前倾或某物倾斜，也可指（使）人或物倚靠在另一人或物之上。

ex.enText: Rays of the sun slanted through the window.

ex.chText: 他把滑雪板略微向右斜了一点。
ex.enText: He slanted his skis a little more to the right.

synonyms.bx: 指某物歪斜或使某物产生一定的角度。

ex.chText: 浴室的地面向排水口倾斜。
ex.enText: The floor of the bathroom slopes down to the drain.
The road slopes sharply at this point.

synonyms.bx: 指地面或其他表面倾斜。

ex.enText: She tilted her head and smiled.

ex.chText: 你可以看见他的嘴角微微翘起。
ex.enText: You can see his mouth tilt upwards slightly at the corners.
The little boy tilted his chair back.

synonyms.bx: 尤指头、下巴等身体部位倾斜或使其倾斜。

tr: an inclined surface connecting two levels

example: the house was built on the side of a mountain

tr: make receptive or willing towards an action or attitude or belief
example: Their language inclines us to believe them
She inclines to the view that people should be allowed to expres their religious beliefs

tr: lower or bend (the head or upper body), as in a nod or bow
example: She inclined her head to the student

tr: bend or turn (one's ear) towards a speaker in order to listen well
example: He inclined his ear to the wise old man

tr: have a tendency or disposition to do or be something
example: She tends to be nervous before her lectures

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ɪn'klaɪn/. The noun is pronounced /'ɪnklaɪn/. 动词读作 /ɪn'klaɪn/,名词读作 /'ɪnklaɪn/。

value.def: If you incline to think or act in a particular way, or if something inclines you to it, you are likely to think or act in that way.

example.ex: I incline to the view that he is right.
example.tran: 我倾向于认为他是正确的。

example.ex: ...the factors which incline us towards particular beliefs...
example.tran: 使我们倾向于相信某些特定信仰的因素

example.ex: Many end up as team leaders, which inclines them to co-operate with the bosses...
example.tran: 很多人最后成为团队领袖,这使得他们易于和上司合作。

example.ex: Those who fail incline to blame the world for their failure.
example.tran: 那些失败者往往将他们的失败归咎于社会。

value.def: If you incline your head, you bend your neck so that your head is leaning forward.

example.ex: Jack inclined his head very slightly.

value.def: An incline is land that slopes at an angle.

example.ex: He came to a halt at the edge of a steep incline.
example.tran: 他在一个陡坡边上停住了。

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + cliv 倾斜；斜坡 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 上斜坡 → 上〔行〕坡
ac 表加强 + cliv 倾斜；斜坡 + ous …的 → 上斜的
de 向下 + clin 倾斜；斜坡 + e → 向下倾斜 → 衰退
de 向下 + cliv 倾斜；斜坡 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 下斜，倾斜
dis 不 + inclined 倾向于 → 不愿的，不喜欢的
in 使… + clin 倾斜；斜坡 + e → 倾斜；倾向
inclin〔e〕倾斜；倾向 + ed 表形容词 → 倾向于…的
pro 向前 + cliv 倾斜；斜坡 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 向前斜 → 倾向
re 回 + clin 倾斜；斜坡 + e → 斜过去 → 斜倚
